# all-services -- aggregate milestone for every auto-starting demo workload
# Reached once each demo service below has started (or failed —
# waits-for never fails this milestone). The interactive console shell
# (tty) is ordered "after: all-services", so the login prompt appears
# once, cleanly, instead of interleaving with the service-start list.
#
# Only services that actually reach STARTED belong here. trigger-test is
# NOT listed: it is a `triggered` service that stays in STARTING until
# `slinitctl trigger trigger-test`, so waiting for it would block this
# milestone forever (and with it the login prompt). boot references it
# instead, where a perpetually-pending waits-for is harmless.
type = internal
depends-on: system-init
waits-for: hello
waits-for: ticker
waits-for: dep-chain
waits-for: cpu-pinned
waits-for: hello-logged
waits-for: logger
waits-for: env-demo
waits-for: graceful-stop
waits-for: cron-demo
waits-for: shared-log
waits-for: app-one
waits-for: app-two
waits-for: runit-svc
waits-for: logfile-demo
waits-for: extra-actions
waits-for: guard-demo
waits-for: rlimit-demo
waits-for: cgroup-demo
waits-for: cgroup-worker
waits-for: socket-demo
waits-for: namespace-demo
waits-for: stop-timeout-demo
waits-for: healthcheck-demo
waits-for: chain-a
waits-for: include-demo
waits-for: sandbox-demo
waits-for: bgprocess-demo
waits-for: vtty-svc
# OpenRC-tools showcase services (added alongside the standalone
# binaries so the boot-time list of demos exercises the new surface).
waits-for: sysctl-demo
waits-for: svc-value-demo
waits-for: ssd-demo
waits-for: supervise-demo
waits-for: einfo-demo
